<P>Mark the End of <HI>Iohn</HI>'s Baptism was, <HI>That
HE might be made manifest to</HI> Israel
<HI>therefore am I come, baptizing with Water:</HI>
So then this was the Service of <HI>Iohn</HI>'s Bap|tism,
and it served for this Purpose, and
to this End, <HI>That Christ might be made ma|nifest.</HI></P>
<P><HI>And so</HI> Iohn <HI>bare Record of him, and
preached him, and not himself; but cryed,</HI>
Behold the Lamb of God; look not at Me; b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1 letter"> hold
not <HI>Me,</HI> nor the Lamb of God and Me; <HI>no, he
